The paper discusses the use of data mining techniques to attract students to Higher Education Institutions (HEI). This involves analyzing data on various advertisement methods and services offered by HEIs to determine the most effective way to attract students. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper involves analyzing and retrieving relevant information. Other likely sub-categories include Data Mining (cs.DM) as the paper uses support and confidence method to analyze the data, Cybernetics (cs.CY) as the paper involves decision-making processes, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as the paper involves analyzing the effectiveness of different advertisement methods, and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as the paper involves understanding the behavior of students and their preferences.
